#SPX / GOLD

Stocks are currently oversold relative to Gold.

We haven’t seen RSI this low on the weekly timeframe since the COVID-19 crash in 2020.

In my opinion, a reversal is likely soon — risk-on assets like stocks and crypto could start moving up, while Gold may cool off for an extended period.

#BANANA / BTC

Looking very bullish — currently holding at the final Fibonacci level before a potential double bottom formation.
Accumulation at this zone could be a strong move for mid to long-term positioning.

#SEI

R:R really good

#GOLD

I’m sure you’ve heard the rumors—China is aggressively buying gold.

The last time we saw something similar was in 2019–2020, when Russia was accumulating gold heavily. Back then, gold made a massive move.

If history repeats itself, we could see a similar surge in price.

Right now, we’re entering what looks like a blow-off top. Nobody knows how high it will go, but I’m personally not buying into a parabolic move. If we top out soon, I believe risk-on assets like crypto could take the spotlight next.

Back in 2020, after gold topped in August, we had a cool-off period until almost the end of 2021. Then came February 2022 and the Russia–Ukraine conflict.

We have to stay alert and be prepared.
